 time of the absence of time, in which the absence of time no longer means eternity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2021) 0aPolitics in literature. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Ideologies / Radicalism.2bisacsh  aBaroque.  aCaribbean Literature.  aCuban Revolution.  aDeconstruction of Time.  aDeconstruction.  aInfrapolitics.  aLezama Lima.  aNeobaroque.  aRevolutionary Political Theory.  aTime.  amodernity.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311072901640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082327410940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823274109423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780823274109.jpg  a978-3-11-072901-6  Fordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK